# TCM — Test Case Management Tool

Internal single-org tool replacing Google Sheets test plans. ~20–25 users, 4 roles, 10+ projects/year, thousands of test cases per project.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** Next.js (App Router) on Vercel
- **UI:** MUI + Material Design 3 principles, dark mode only
- **Animation:** Framer Motion — purposeful micro-interactions only
- **Backend/DB/Auth/Storage:** Supabase (Postgres, Auth, Storage, Realtime, Edge Functions)
- **Auth:** Google OAuth 2.0 only (company Google Workspace)

## Core Data Hierarchy

`projects` → `suites` (with prefix, e.g. "SR") → `test_cases` (display_id "SR-1") → `test_steps`

Test execution: `test_runs` → `test_run_cases` → `execution_results` (per step × platform × browser)

## Roles (hierarchy: Admin > SDET > QA Engineer > Viewer)

- **Admin:** Full access + user management
- **SDET:** QA Engineer + automation integration + CI/CD
- **QA Engineer:** Test case CRUD, execution, reporting, suite management
- **Viewer:** Read-only everywhere — no edit controls visible, no write API access

## MVP Features (N1–N8)

N1: CSV Import | N2: Test Case CRUD | N3: Execution Tracking | N4: Project/Suite Mgmt | N5: Reporting | N6: Grid View (MUI X Data Grid) | N7: User Mgmt | N8: Playwright Webhook

## Forward-Compatibility (build for now, ship later)

- `metadata` JSONB on test_cases for S6 custom fields
- `tags` text[] on test_cases for S2 smoke/regression filtering
- `integrations` table placeholder for S4 Slack / S5 GitLab
- `comments`, `activity_log`, `notifications` tables for S7 collaboration
- Webhook API extensible for S1/S3 (Playwright, k6, JMeter)
- `test_case_type` enum extensible for S3 performance tests

